text:

author: Ertiza Abbas
text: If you're tired of soulless sweat factories, run (or saunter, no rush) to Anytime Fitness Lower Pierce. It's transformed my "ugh, exercise" into "yes, this is my happy place." Five stars aren't enough. Thank you for reminding me that wellness can feel this good, this real, this joyful. üíñ #FitnessFamily #LowerPierceLove #AnyTimeFitness #Singapore

author: Sihan Goi
text: Dropped by on a Tuesday afternoon and it was rather quiet. The gym is small, but is quite new and neat, and also has pretty much all the equipment I need for a good workout, especially in the free weights section. 1 rack, 1 small platform, 2 Ziva barbells that spin, 2 sets of coloured bumper plates, other rubberized plates. There are some specialty bars too - 1 short bar and 1 safety bar. Lots of plate loaded machines and a few different pulley attachments. Dumbbells up to 50kg. However, there's very little redundancy. For example, only 1 rack, so if someone is benching, you can't squat, and vice versa. It would've been nice if another rack could be squeezed in somewhere - perhaps make it 2 racks + attached platforms and 2 other bars, and remove the existing small platform - not sure if it'll fit but it sure would make it easier to train when it's crowded. There's a locker area but I didn't see if there were shower areas or toilets. Parking is along the road outside or the public carpark just across the street.

author: darani daran
text:
I had a fantastic experience at Anytime Fitness in Lower Pierce, Singapore. The gym is spacious and well equipped, providing a wide range of high-quality equipment to cater to different fitness needs. The facility is clean and well maintained, creating a pleasant environment for workouts.

The staff members were friendly and attentive, always ready to assist and offer guidance.

Additionally, the gym's convenient operating hours allowed me to work out at my own pace.

Overall, I highly recommend Anytime Fitness in Lower Pierce for its excellent facilities and welcoming atmosphere....highly recommended

Looking forward to my gym journey with AF @ lower pierce.

author: Trevor Sze
text: I was on a quest to check out ALL 120+ locations of AF and i now have, and this one is one of my favourites! Despite not being one of those mega sized ones like City Hall or Chai Chee, here at Lower Pierce there's a really nice vibe to it. Machines (though not as extensive as the bigger places) are complete enough, able to target every body part, making it possible for satisfactory workout sessions without much effort to compromise. There is enough space between machines so as to not feel oppressed (like other locations can be). Floor to ceiling windows on 2 sides allow plenty of natural light in, at the same time making it safer to workout at night. The cardio machines face a quiet neighbourhood park while the proximity to the many shophouse eateries and a good hawker centre, makes your gym trip even more pleasant and one you look forward to. Being in a quaint and cozy neighbourhood helps you relax and unwind with a focused workout, unlike the stressful mall and office district locations. This place is well worth a special visit to!

author: Xavier Ng
text: As I walked into Anytime Fitness Lower Pierce, I was immediately greeted by the friendly and welcoming atmosphere of the gym. The staff, especially Christopher, exuded a genuine sense of warmth and hospitality that instantly put me at ease. Christopher offered to give me a tour of the facility. His knowledge and passion for fitness were evident as he guided me through the state-of-the-art equipment and explained the various workout options available to me. Throughout my workout session, Christopher was always on hand to offer assistance, encouragement, and helpful tips to optimize my fitness routine. His positive attitude and enthusiasm were truly infectious, motivating me to push myself further and achieve my fitness goals. What stood out to me the most was Christopher's genuine care and commitment to ensuring that I had a positive and productive gym experience. Whether it was adjusting my form during exercises or simply checking in to see how I was doing, his personalized attention made me feel valued as a member of the gym community.Thanks to Christopher and the team at Anytime Fitness Lower Pierce, my gym sessions became more than just a workout‚Äîthey became a source of inspiration and empowerment. I left the gym feeling invigorated, motivated, and grateful for the exceptional service and support I received. I can confidently say that Anytime Fitness Lower Pierce, with its top-notch facilities and dedicated staff like Christopher, has become my go-to place for achieving my fitness goals.

author: Toh Hong Rui
text:

Staff is friendly during stuffed hours, but as always for anytime fitness outlets, spoiled by people who either don't bring towels, or don't wipe down the equipment after usage, or worse, both. Makes me also realise why should I be so considerate to bring my towel and wipe down the equipment?

Tip: wiping the equipment before you use them is more important than wiping after usage.
